                                         CAPE TOWN - As part of ongoing awareness campaigns, the City of Cape Town will be engaging with members of the public at malls and on beaches around matters of personal safety.  Among a list of safety tips, officials have urged residents to be alert while using ATMs, especially in secluded spots or late at night.  The city's Zelda Martin said: “The city’s metro department appeals to the public to keep their guard up as we head into the full festive season swing. Vigilance is key, both in shopping malls and other places of public interests, on the road and also at home.”